s to refocus attention on the wide variety of strategic alliances they generated in their quests for freedom, equality and profit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBlack peoplexMigrationsxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlack peoplexRace identityzCaribbean AreaxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlack peoplexRace identityzGulf Coast (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aBlack peoplezCaribbean AreaxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlack peoplezGulf Coast (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aBlacks -- Caribbean Area -- History -- 19th century. 0aBlacks -- Gulf Coast (U.S.) -- History -- 19th century. 0aBlacks -- Migrations -- History -- 19th century. 0aBlacks -- Race identity -- Caribbean Area -- History -- 19th century. 0aBlacks -- Race identity -- Gulf Coast (U.S.) -- History -- 19th century. 0aBlacksxMigrationsxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlacksxRace identityzCaribbean AreaxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlacksxRace identityzGulf Coast (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aBlackszCaribbean AreaxHistoryy19th century. 0aBlackszGulf Coast (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aHaiti -- History -- Revolution, 1791-1804 -- Influence. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  a19th century history.  aafrican american demographics.  aafrican american studies.  ablack history.  ablack oppression.  abooks for history lovers.  acaribbean literature.  acivil rights.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  afrench culture.  afrench history.  afrench politics.  ahaitian history.  ahaitian revolution.  ahardships of minorities.  ahistory and politics.  ahistory.  ahome school history books.  ainterdisciplinary study.  alatin american literature.  aliterary criticism.  amigration of haitian culture.  anonfiction history.  apolitics.08iTitle is part of e